# Walkthrough - Voice-to-Text Integration

I have successfully integrated voice-to-text search functionality across the Taqeem platform. This enhancement allows users to perform search queries using their voice, improving accessibility and user experience.

## Changes Made

### 1. Premium Landing Page (`saudi-courses-platform.html`)
- Integrated a microphone button within the hero search input.
- Added CSS for the microphone button, including a pulsing animation when "listening".
- Implemented `startVoiceSearch()` using the Web Speech API.
- Added automatic language detection (Arabic/English) for voice recognition.

### 2. Main Platform (`taqeem-platform.html`)
- Added the microphone button to the main search bar in the hero section.
- Replicated the styling and logic from the landing page to ensure consistency.
- Connected voice output to the existing suggestion and search filtering systems.

### 3. Design System (`taqeem-design-system.html`)
- Added the voice search component to the design system's search section for future reference and consistency.
- Standardized the `startVoiceSearch` implementation to work with the design system's specific translation keys (`sPH`).

